<heading bold="true" box="[264,1176,1723,1749]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,1176,1723,1749]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName authority="Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo" authorityName="Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo" box="[264,872,1723,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrajiboiensis" status="new species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,573,1723,1749]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Ommatius serrajiboiensis</emphasis>
Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[879,1023,1723,1749]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[1039,1167,1723,1749]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[315,1283,728,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[289,1298,689,1751]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Ommatius serrajiboiensis Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo, sp. nov., Holotype male. 7. Right gonostylus. 8. Aedeagus lateral. 9. Aedeagus ventral. 10. Male terminalia dorsal. 11. Male terminalia ventral. 12. male terminalia lateral. 13. Right hind tibia with a spurlike bristle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158816/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Figs. 
<number box="[1107,1167,1723,1749]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="10.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="7.0">7–13</number>
</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1325,1798,1904]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Male. Length: body, 13.0 mm; wing 10.0 mm. Body dark brown to blackish. Face golden with six brown bristles mystax; 
<collectionCode box="[650,735,1838,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FHWR</collectionCode>
<number box="[745,755,1838,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
/1.8mm. Palpus yellowish setose. 
<collectionCode box="[1167,1249,1838,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FWLR</collectionCode>
<number box="[1258,1268,1838,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
/5.8. Occiput with seven dark brown postocular bristles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,284,630]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Mesonotum with four long dorsocentral bristles in each row; two notopleural bristles; one postalar bristle; one subalare bristle; prominent anepimeral bristle absent. Scutellum with two stout marginal bristles. Pleuron mostly yellowish tomentose. Wing with costal margin slightly dilated.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,284,630]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Legs mostly yellow, fore and middle femora with apical one­third brownish. Mid femora with a pale, long, thin, preapical, dorsoposterior seta; 
<collectingCountry box="[951,1010,484,510]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Hind</collectingCountry>
femora with five blackish bristles and one pale basal bristle. 
<collectionCode box="[672,775,524,550]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">HFWLR</collectionCode>
<number box="[783,793,524,550]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
/3.3. 
<collectingCountry box="[858,917,524,550]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia with spurlike bristle apically (
<figureCitation box="[273,359,564,590]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[315,1283,728,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[289,1298,689,1751]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Ommatius serrajiboiensis Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo, sp. nov., Holotype male. 7. Right gonostylus. 8. Aedeagus lateral. 9. Aedeagus ventral. 10. Male terminalia dorsal. 11. Male terminalia ventral. 12. male terminalia lateral. 13. Right hind tibia with a spurlike bristle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158816/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[327,359,564,590]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Fore and middle tarsi with basal segments in part yellowish; fore tarsus with one yellow bristle in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158816/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" targetBox="[315,1283,728,1735]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1777,1870]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,452,1777,1801]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">FIGURES 7–13.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo" authorityName="Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo" box="[462,1006,1777,1801]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrajiboiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[462,739,1778,1801]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ommatius serrajiboiensis</emphasis>
Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1023,1111,1777,1800]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, Holotype male. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1302,1315,1777,1801]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">7</emphasis>
. Right gonostylus. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[464,477,1812,1836]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">8</emphasis>
. Aedeagus lateral. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[689,702,1812,1836]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">9</emphasis>
. Aedeagus ventral. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[922,948,1812,1836]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">10</emphasis>
. Male terminalia dorsal. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1227,1251,1812,1836]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">11</emphasis>
. Male terminalia ventral. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[466,493,1846,1870]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">12</emphasis>
. male terminalia lateral. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[759,786,1846,1870]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">13</emphasis>
. Right hind tibia with a spurlike bristle.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1324,284,910]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Abdomen with dark brown tomentum in dorsal view; sides of tergites and sternites 
<number pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1– 4</number>
, with pale yellowish vestiture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1324,284,910]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Terminalia blackish. Epandrium with truncate apex, with posterior acute projection (
<figureCitation box="[273,354,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[315,1283,728,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[289,1298,689,1751]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Ommatius serrajiboiensis Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo, sp. nov., Holotype male. 7. Right gonostylus. 8. Aedeagus lateral. 9. Aedeagus ventral. 10. Male terminalia dorsal. 11. Male terminalia ventral. 12. male terminalia lateral. 13. Right hind tibia with a spurlike bristle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158816/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[323,354,404,430]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
); lateral margin round in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[821,911,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[315,1283,728,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[289,1298,689,1751]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Ommatius serrajiboiensis Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo, sp. nov., Holotype male. 7. Right gonostylus. 8. Aedeagus lateral. 9. Aedeagus ventral. 10. Male terminalia dorsal. 11. Male terminalia ventral. 12. male terminalia lateral. 13. Right hind tibia with a spurlike bristle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158816/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[878,911,404,430]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium shield­like with the anterior margin rounded, apex triangular and posterior margin with pair of lateral acute projections (
<figureCitation box="[411,498,484,510]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[315,1283,728,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[289,1298,689,1751]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Ommatius serrajiboiensis Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo, sp. nov., Holotype male. 7. Right gonostylus. 8. Aedeagus lateral. 9. Aedeagus ventral. 10. Male terminalia dorsal. 11. Male terminalia ventral. 12. male terminalia lateral. 13. Right hind tibia with a spurlike bristle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158816/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[467,498,484,510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonostylus subtriangular, with acute projection at the apex (
<figureCitation box="[1235,1308,484,510]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[315,1283,728,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[289,1298,689,1751]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Ommatius serrajiboiensis Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo, sp. nov., Holotype male. 7. Right gonostylus. 8. Aedeagus lateral. 9. Aedeagus ventral. 10. Male terminalia dorsal. 11. Male terminalia ventral. 12. male terminalia lateral. 13. Right hind tibia with a spurlike bristle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158816/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[1291,1308,484,510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite with two blade­like projections nearest the apex in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1308,524,550]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[315,1283,728,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[289,1298,689,1751]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Ommatius serrajiboiensis Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo, sp. nov., Holotype male. 7. Right gonostylus. 8. Aedeagus lateral. 9. Aedeagus ventral. 10. Male terminalia dorsal. 11. Male terminalia ventral. 12. male terminalia lateral. 13. Right hind tibia with a spurlike bristle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158816/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[1277,1308,524,550]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Apex of the terminal filament of the aedeagus acute in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1116,1191,564,590]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[315,1283,728,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[289,1298,689,1751]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Ommatius serrajiboiensis Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo, sp. nov., Holotype male. 7. Right gonostylus. 8. Aedeagus lateral. 9. Aedeagus ventral. 10. Male terminalia dorsal. 11. Male terminalia ventral. 12. male terminalia lateral. 13. Right hind tibia with a spurlike bristle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158816/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[1175,1191,564,590]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
); aedeagal sheath with anterior margin curved in ventral view and with two small blade­like lateral projections on the base of the edeagal filament (
<figureCitation box="[849,924,644,670]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[315,1283,728,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[289,1298,689,1751]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Ommatius serrajiboiensis Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo, sp. nov., Holotype male. 7. Right gonostylus. 8. Aedeagus lateral. 9. Aedeagus ventral. 10. Male terminalia dorsal. 11. Male terminalia ventral. 12. male terminalia lateral. 13. Right hind tibia with a spurlike bristle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158816/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[907,924,644,670]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
); aedeagal apodeme with posteroventral margin straight at base, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[831,902,684,710]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[315,1283,728,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[289,1298,689,1751]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Ommatius serrajiboiensis Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo, sp. nov., Holotype male. 7. Right gonostylus. 8. Aedeagus lateral. 9. Aedeagus ventral. 10. Male terminalia dorsal. 11. Male terminalia ventral. 12. male terminalia lateral. 13. Right hind tibia with a spurlike bristle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158816/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[886,902,684,710]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
