<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1324,284,910]" box="[312,1020,804,830]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Etymology. This species is named for the collection locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1324,284,910]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName box="[430,733,844,869]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrajiboiensis">
<emphasis box="[430,733,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Ommatius serrajiboiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily recognized from congeners by the combined characters of the terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[672,801,884,910]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 13" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1777,1801]" captionTargetBox="[315,1283,728,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[289,1298,689,1751]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 13. Ommatius serrajiboiensis Vieira, Castro &amp; Bravo, sp. nov., Holotype male. 7. Right gonostylus. 8. Aedeagus lateral. 9. Aedeagus ventral. 10. Male terminalia dorsal. 11. Male terminalia ventral. 12. male terminalia lateral. 13. Right hind tibia with a spurlike bristle." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158816/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Figs. 
<number box="[739,801,884,910]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="9.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="7.0">7–12</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
